{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer\/fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This parameter defines the range for the fade-out effect before an automatic content cutoff on pitched map views. Fade out is implemented by scaling down and removing buildings in the fade range in a staggered fashion. Opacity is not changed. The fade range is expressed in relation to the height of the map view. A value of 1.0 indicates that the content is faded to the same extent as the map’s height in pixels, while a value close to zero represents a sharp cutoff. When the value is set to 0.0, the cutoff is completely disabled. Note: The property has no effect on the map if terrain is enabled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Default value: 0. Value range: [0, 1]","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10MapboxMaps18FillExtrusionLayerV04fillD15CutoffFadeRangeAA5ValueOySdGSgvp","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Value","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10MapboxMaps5ValueO"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"},{"text":">?","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"MapboxMaps"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/Value","preciseIdentifier":"s:10MapboxMaps5ValueO","text":"Value","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"type